      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is a white-label SEO tool?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">A white-label SEO tool lets you deliver SEO services under your own brand — your logo, your domain, your client's invoice — while the tool does the work behind the scenes. Some provide reporting and dashboards (SE Ranking, AgencyAnalytics). Others provide fulfillment — actual content, links, or local SEO work (theStacc, The HOTH). The best agencies combine both.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What's the highest-margin white-label SEO service?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Content resale through theStacc offers the highest margins on this list: $99/month cost, $1,500/month resell price, 93% margin. Add Local SEO and Social Media modules and your cost rises to ~$167/month. A $2,500/month client package leaves you with $2,333 in monthly margin per client.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What's the difference between white-label fulfillment and white-label reporting?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Fulfillment tools produce deliverables your client can see — blog articles, GBP posts, backlinks. Reporting tools produce dashboards and PDFs showing how those deliverables are performing. Most agencies need both. theStacc is the fulfillment engine. SE Ranking, AgencyAnalytics, or DashThis sits on top for reporting.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can I resell theStacc's content under my agency's brand?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes. theStacc publishes content to your client's site. Your client sees their blog updating with SEO articles, their Google Business Profile staying active, and their social media publishing — all under your agency's results. They don't see theStacc. You price the service at your rate and keep the margin.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How many clients do I need to break even on white-label SEO tools?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">At $99/month for theStacc, one client paying $200/month covers your costs. One client at $500/month generates $401 in profit. The math scales quickly: 10 clients on the Blog + Local bundle ($167/month cost, $2,000/month resell) nets $18,330 per month in margin.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Do I need a white-label dashboard for clients to log in to?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Not necessarily. Many agencies deliver white-label SEO as a service — clients just see results (rankings moving, content publishing, GBP active) and receive branded monthly reports. If you want a client-facing portal, pair theStacc with AgencyAnalytics or DashThis. If clients just want results, theStacc's output speaks for itself.</div>
